Program.cs
Purpose:  
Provides the main user interface and controls program flow.

Responsibilities:

Display menu

Allow user to create goals

Allow user to record events

Allow user to save/load goals

Display score and level

Exit program cleanly

Code
---------------------------------------------------------
|                     Program                            |
---------------------------------------------------------
| + Main()                                               |
---------------------------------------------------------

1. Show Main Menu
The program repeatedly displays:

Create New Goal

List Goals

Record Event

Save Goals

Load Goals

Quit

User selects an option by entering a number.

2. Create a New Goal
User selects goal type:

Simple Goal

Eternal Goal

Checklist Goal

Program asks for:

Name

Description

Points

(Checklist only) Target count

(Checklist only) Bonus points

GoalManager_RP stores the new goal.

3. List Goals
Program displays:

[ ] or [X] for completion

For checklist goals: Completed X/Y times

For eternal goals: [∞] indicator

User presses Enter to return to menu.

4. Record Event
User selects a goal from the list.

Program:

Calls RecordEvent_RP() on that goal

Adds returned points to score

Displays points earned

Displays updated score and level

5. Save Goals
Program asks for a filename.

GoalManager_RP writes:

Score

Each goal’s string representation

6. Load Goals
Program asks for a filename.

GoalManager_RP:

Reads score

Reconstructs each goal from file

Restores checklist progress and completion

7. Quit
Program exits cleanly.

8. Gamification (Exceeds Requirements)
User levels up every 1000 points

Level displayed on main menu

Level displayed after recording events